            </rs>: He was taken going to dispose of part of it, by the Beadle of Covent-garden, who knew him well enough to suspect him: he had several pieces of Gold about him, when apprehended; and amongst divers other things, a silver and gold Bowl, and a Crucifix of Gold. After he was <rs id="t16760823-8-verdict28" type="verdictDescription">
